17/01/2003
KABUL, Afghanistan -- Turkey and Afghanistan signed a military agreement Thursday (16 January), the first of its kind between the two Muslim countries since 1921. 
Turkey currently plays a leading role in the International Security Assistance Force, which provides peacekeeping operations in Afghanistan. 
Under the agreement, Turkey would provide help in military training, technical and scientific fields and the training of personal security guards. 
(Anadolu Agency, AFP, BBC, Dunya - 16/01/03)
